subject: TAK-594/DNL593: 12-Month Cohort Queries
body:
Hi David,

My team has processed the final batch of query resolutions for the TAK-594/DNL593 12-month cohort. Our system shows zero outstanding queries.

Can you please provide a final confirmation from the biostatistics side that you are aligned and we are ready to proceed with database lock procedures?

Thanks,

Maria Garcia
Data Management Lead
Denali Therapeutics

subject: Re: TAK-594/DNL593: 12-Month Cohort Queries
body:
Hi Maria,

Thanks for the update. I've reviewed the final data listings and can confirm that biostatistics has no further queries. We are clear for database lock.

Great work by your team to get this closed out.

Best,

David Chen
Lead Biostatistician
Denali Therapeutics

subject: Re: TAK-594/DNL593: 12-Month Cohort Queries
body:
Hi Alex,

With David's confirmation, we are officially ready for the 12-month cohort database lock.

Below is a draft communication for you to send to the joint project team to formally announce this milestone. Please review and send at your convenience.

---

**Subject:** TAK-594/DNL593: 12-Month Cohort Database Ready for Lock

**To:** Takeda-Denali JPT Distribution List

Dear Team,

This email serves as formal notification that all data queries for the 12-month cohort of the TAK-594/DNL593 FTD-GRN study have been resolved. The clinical database is clean and ready for lock.

We are targeting End of Day this Friday, May 24th, for the final lock to occur.

Thank you to all team members for your diligence in reaching this key milestone.

Best regards,

Alex Johnson

---

Thanks,

Maria
